<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/asp.79.e66978.figure10>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Habitus of male Colobopsis and Camponotus; (A, B) heads in full-face (dorsal) view; (C, D) genitalia in dorsolateral oblique view; (E, F) bodies in profile view; (G, H) wings in ventral view; scale bars: A, B = 0.5 mm, C, D = 0.1 mm, E-G = 1.0 mm. A, C, E, G: Colobopsis species indet., from Fijian radiation (CASENT 0171201). B, D, F, H: Camponotus planus (CASENT 0173220, image from AntWeb [www. antweb. org], photographed by April Nobile). Abbreviations: atVIII = abdominal tergum VIII (metasomal VII), asIX = abdominal sternum IX (metasomal VIII), ce = cerci, gc = gonocoxa, gs = gonostylus, Mf 1 = first free medial vein abscissa, psa = penial sclerite ventral apex, Rsf 1 = first free radial sector vein abscissa, vo = volsella." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/533438" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

